## Archiving With Retrofit

By default, Retrofit will use a cache interceptor to intercept requests and save them to temporary cache in memory. This is especially useful when dealing with APIs that have lots of static content that you donâ€™t want to repeatedly get from the server. If the saved content does not change, you can simply ask the Retrofit cache for the content. This is very helpful when presenting information in an application or showing a list on a dialog without going through the main activity/screen. More common use cases would include offering offline dictionary word definition lookups, as well as providing a collection of commonly used (or useless) URL resources as dynamically accessible posts, etc.

### Example: offline documentation lookup

CachedRetrofit t = CachedRetrofit.builder()
.build();
IRetrofitAPI_ wiki = t.create(IRetrofitAPI_.class);
Uri uri = Uri.parse("https://source.android.com/documentation/index.html").buildUpon()
.build();
Response response = wiki.getDocumentation(uri);
